Thousands of South Africans have been on the housing waiting list for years. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Thousands of South Africans have been on the housing waiting list for years. Growing impatient with the human settlements department, many have been taking to the streets. READ: SA housing Crisis | Police use teargas on protesting residents This week, residents of Swaneville, in Krugersdorp clashed with police while protesting. They say they're tired of being backyard dwellers. eNCA Lindokuhle Xulu spoke to one of the protesters and filled a report in the video above.